<subSubSection id="BFE88CB7F15A2F3A7482BEA9A2E098EE" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F74DDF3CF15A2F3A7482BEA9A2E098EE" blockId="5.[151,1437,266,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A7482BEA9A23E9980" bold="true" box="[197,318,1755,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="30F2A4BFF15A2F3A76EDBEA9A0D09980" authority="Zaitzev" authorityName="Zaitzev" box="[682,976,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesasiatica">
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A76EDBEA9A0599981" box="[682,857,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. mesasiatica</emphasis>
(Zaitzev)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the hyaline part of cell 
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A759CBF71A10F9869" box="[475,527,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">cu-a</emphasis>
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A7649BF61A1169854" box="[526,534,1811,1825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number id="413ACD1BF15A2F3A7649BF61A1169854" box="[526,534,1811,1825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</emphasis>
smaller, the epiphallus distinctly narrowing at middle, and the distiphallus subquadrate in dorsal view. In 
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A7641BF5CA1BC9832" box="[518,700,1838,1863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="30F2A4BFF15A2F3A7641BF5CA1B89832" box="[518,696,1838,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesasiatica">H. mesasiatica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the hyaline apical part of cell 
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A706BBF5CA7609832" box="[1068,1120,1838,1863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">cu-a</emphasis>
<emphasis id="C586032EF15A2F3A7018BF4CA7679839" box="[1119,1127,1854,1868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number id="413ACD1BF15A2F3A7018BF4CA7679839" box="[1119,1127,1854,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</emphasis>
is rather large, more than half of the infuscate part; the epiphallus is slightly narrowing at middle, and the distiphallus is subtriangular in dorsal view (
<bibRefCitation id="9363A2CDF15A2F3A7569BFF3A2D398EE" author="Zaitzev" box="[302,467,1921,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="23" refString="Zaitzev, V. F. (1962) [The fauna of bee flies (Diptera, Bombyliidae) of eastern Pamir]. Izvestyia Otdela Biologicheskoi Nauk, Akademiia Nauk Tadzhikskoi SSR, 1 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="1962">
Zaitzev, 
<number id="413ACD1BF15A2F3A75D3BFF3A2D398EE" box="[404,467,1921,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1962.0">1962</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
